A pregnant woman was among occupants rescued from a collapsed single-storey building at Ajaye-Alagbado area of Lagos State on Tuesday. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the woman was rescued by the locals at about 4.45 p.m before the arrival of the Lagos State Fire Service. The woman was taken to Ile Epo General Hospital in Oke Odo Local Council Development Area in Lagos. As of the time of filing this report, men of the fire service have cordoned off the rubble and were busy searching for others trapped in the rubble.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .